Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/4%tsp}. Trim the @green beans{80%grams}.

When boiling, add the @egg noodle nest{125%grams} and green beans to the water and cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to stop them sticking together.

Meanwhile, halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Cut the @lime{1} into wedges. Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Roughly chop the @coriander{1%bunch} (stalks and all).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{1%pack} and cook until browned all over, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Once browned, add the sliced pepper and @sliced mushrooms{180%grams}. Fry until slightly charred and soft, ~{5-6%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Add the garlic and @Thai style spice mix{1%sachet} to the pan. Cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the @soy sauce{25%milliliters}, @ketjap manis{50%grams} and @water for the sauce{50%milliliters} to the veg.

Stir together, then add the @mangetout{} and cook until the sauce has thickened slightly, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir the cooked noodles and green beans through the fragrant sauce and toss until well combined.

Share the sticky Thai style noodles between your #bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the @salted peanuts{25%grams} and coriander.

Squeeze over some lime juice from a lime wedge to finish.

Serve with any remaining lime wedges alongside. Enjoy!